Columbia Health Loss

Summary

Deaths

One metric of disease burden is the number of deaths. Below is a barchart of the top 10 diseases that cause the most health loss in Colombia:

YLLs

Another metric of disease burden is Years of Life Lost (YLLs). This measures the years of potential life lost due to premature deaths. Below is a bar chart of the top 10 diseases as measured by YLLs.

YLDs

Another metric of disease burden is Years of Lived with Disability (YLDs). This measures the years of potential life lost due to living with a disability. Below is a bar chart of the top 10 diseases as measured by YLDs.

DALYs

Lastly, another metric of disease burden is Disability Adjusted Life Years (DALYs). This measures the overall disease burden, expressed the years of potential life lost due to ill-health, disability, or premature death. DALYs combines mortality and morbidity into one metric. Below is a bar chart of the top 10 diseases as measured by DALYs.

Comparison of Asthma

Below is a barchart of different health metrics comparing asthma. Based on the barchart, asthma has the most ylds and the least deaths. This means asthma is not a deadly health condition as not many people die from this cause. This is also shown for the ylls comparison because not many lifetime years are lost from asthma. In contrast, a higher percentage of people end up living with asthma, which explains the large percentage of ylds. Lastly, the DALYs tells us that the overall burden for asthma is about 1.7%.
